 same table. It was a long one and underneath there was a ledge like that and I used to sit at one side on't floor and me brother - me other brother'd be at that side and we used to have that for a little table. On this ledge underneath. 'Cos there was no
 
room on top for t'others when there was my father and my mother and the other two was at that side and you was underneath. I'll never forget - I think I've got the mark yet got the mark yet. Me father was having - having his dinner and I puts me hand unde
r
 his knees like that and took a piece - a piece of meat off his plate. Well, he didn't see me first time. So the next time I comes again but - he had the knife and he chopped me fingers - he nearly chopped me three fingers off. And I've got them now - I'v
e got the - I've got the mark -
