Oh that's what is was for - children. You went - on a lorry. You didn't go in a train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You went on a lorry?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Horse lorries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And they took you to where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Southport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did they change the horses on the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes, yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
The - there was that and then there was John Street Hall you know. They used to take us away. Yes. Well - that was - that was in John Street. That was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Is this Pendleton or Manchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Pendleton. Go d
own Allen Street way and you'll come to it and - John Street was on the left hand side - you come along Broad Street it was on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 right hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was it a mission or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And they used to take you away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, oh yes. We used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Had you got to attend the mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, we used to go - and we used to get food there and all. Used to get - soup and stuff at night time and - and - then they used to take us to see the others club you know, it was called the Cind
erella Club - that was in Evers Street. And they used to take us to the theatres. Yes, oh yes. Ragged school it was called. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Tell me what happened when you went for soup - did you go every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh no, not every day, was only certain nights we had to go then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Anyone could go could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. Only they was a chil - children you know. And - they used to have turns there - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 comedians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  used to come you know and - bit of things like that. And we used to get a bag of stuff coming out - a cake and orange or something like that in a bag.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And eat it on the way home or did you take it home to mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh we - we - we'd - used to hold it. Never - never - never ever ate it at home when we got home. In fact sometimes they never knew
 we was gone. We never used to tell 'em you know. Off we'd go. Else off to baths and, you know, she never knew anything about it. Now when anyone - when anybody - there was no ambulances then you know - now, if anyone was pulled out of the cut - that's th
e
 canal you know, drowned, they used to fetch 'em home on a stretcher. Police used to fetch 'em and you - right through the streets - all the way into - down to Police Street and there was a - they took 'em in there you see. Had a mortuary there. And - the
 - you never see them after that - they was took 'em in. But every morning we used to go to - the police station see if anybody was been - locked up -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 
 the drunks and all like that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well just - down Police Street it was on the left hand side - the - whatsit 
- this fence was the other side. And - we used to stand there see who was - who was knocked off that night, you know, who was locked up. All the children - we used to go there see these old fellows fetched out, such as Brockie Price, he was - he was locke
d up about sixty times you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Drunk. Oh - the drunks, aye. You could see them. Aye, Brockie Price and - and then in then days you know they had what they call - it was a - they had their photograph in the pub - in the pubs you know. 
Anyone what was - blacklisted, that was it. Now, if - if he got that - if they got locked up for a certain number of times they used to what they call blacklist 'em. And the photograph, the magistrates ordered the photograph to be put in the public house.
 
Now that man was barred, you see. He was barred for - for being drunk. He was not - wouldn't allow him to be served - he couldn't - they darent' serve him. And that's what the - the customers - the - the pub - boss, he used to see you. When a man walked i
n to see what his - his photo was there or not. If it was he wouldn't serve him. He'd get noted that way you see. That Brockie Price and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What was Brockie short for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
We called him Brockie for n- his face was well, pock marked you know. Call him
 - call him Brockie Price, aye. Never worked you know, he was always on the scrounge. And ; always getting locked up and - sleep anywhere, in fact you see, he was - even if it was only fourpence a night he - before they did a - before he got his - paid hi
s lodgings he - he'd get - he'd have a couple of pints. Sleep out. He used to call it dosing out you know. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 Did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  you get a lot of people doss out down Hankey Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, aye, lots of 'em. Yes. Lots of 'em used to do that. And they're - and there was Pric and there was Ryan. Oh there was several persons got arrested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were there lots of fights down Hankey Park when the men got drunk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh aye, there - well, they used to get eight pints for a shilling you see. If they had a shilling - it was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 It made them fighting drink did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. And they used to schooldrive 'em up you know, what they call frog march them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 The police did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. They'd no - no conveyances then not same as the police car and fetch 'em up. They
 had to drag 'em up. And - I never forget - a man 1 man got a month through me. Same thing. It was Jack - Oakley his name was. And he was always one of them. Always drunk and drunk. Well, they caught me at the corner of the street you know, and they used 
to take us to station to book us, you see, and they taking me up - up Hankey Park - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was this for loitering again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Loitering - used to call it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 loitering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 . Stand at the corner of the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Loitering with intent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, yes. So - he 
- Jack Oakley comes round you see to policeman and - what you taking him for he says. You know, in a boasting way. So he lets go of me and grabs - grabs Jack Oakley and he takes him up 'cos he knew - he knew }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 he knew where I lived you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 So he charged him with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 rescuing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 . Drunk and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 rescuing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 . He - he got a month. Without - without a fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
You told me you were put in Strangeways for seven days - tell me what it was like in prison when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No - well, we was in the - we was in the cells li
ke - oh - everyone was all in separate cells you know. Oh yes, sat in our own cell, yes. And - there was one; officer - one - it were - we were in the juveniles you see. Juveniles. Well they used - used to fetch us out and they didn't used to take us in t
he exercise ground where all the prisoners was doing time - but you see, we used to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  had - in lobby. And you - he used to train us in there you see. That was our exercise you see. Was exercised every day like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were they good to you and was the food good?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well - you got - you got a little collar bread - brown bread in the morning and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Just bread or something else as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And - just bread. Nothing on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh no, nothing on it. Used to brown loaf and a pint of skillie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What was skillie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Porridge. We called it skillie. They always called it skillie. Yes. And - I tell you the first time I went was when that - I catch them at the time when he sent me down for Friday for three days and I was out next 
morning. Well, anyway, next time he - give me seven days the next time. This is what - I done - remember getting the exercise you see there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did you have for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well you'd get - about - about three potatoes in - in their jackets you kn
ow. Skins on. And - different days, had soup one day, soup and potatoes. And didn't get any bread with you know - you had your bread at morning. And - and - sometimes - it'd be kidney beans and so and so and all like this you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh n
o meat - get meat on one day. It was called meat without bone - it's a stew like - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You didn't get meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Just like water was it, this stew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes. But - I believe it's different now altogether you know what - b
ecause it was terrible. The treadmill was going then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9836352\charrsid16398449 What\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  a treadmill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
The treadmill was a - it was a large wheel. And - it was partitions - each man to stand in and he had to keep his feet going with the treadmill you see and that treadmill was grinding corn. For to make - they made their own meal you know at one time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How long did you have to stay on the treadmill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, for the - thirteen times you see - well, about quarter of an hour on and a quarter of an hour off you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 They didn't make you - boys do it surely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, oh no, but they did - it was going for the men, you see, the treadmill was going then, but - didn't put - us on the tradmill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did they make you do during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well - they ma
de us - sometimes we made mailbags you know, sewing mailbags. And - some - post office bags there was. And - had a - you had about two to do a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did the warders treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh they - they was very strict with us. Very strict. Worse than te
achers in school and all like that. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 They didn't hit you or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No. But the police did. The police. -The - you see, if we were stood at the corner of Hankey Park and this - policeman come and he couldn't get you with - if he got near
 you he'd knock you down with his cape. Down you - down you'd go and you couldn't retaliate or anything like that because if you offered to do him that - was - he'd put it down as - drunk and disorderly you know and assaulting the police, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 But they only hit you with the cape - they didn't hit you in any other way?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, as they got older - they couldn't catch you see - was a bit too quick for 'em but he got his - he'd come round the corner with his cape and he'd knock one of us down you see or - or perhaps two if he got us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did he hurt you if he caught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, no, didn't after. Sometimes you went a bit - it would be - well he'd used - men you know, when they got them in the station, but they didn't do us - we was young you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did they do to the men in the station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
It all depends whether they was retaliating with the police you know, if they set about the police when they were supposed - before the got him up there. They wouldn't ill use him in the street but w
hen they got him in the police station they used to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 With their fists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Hit 'em with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3492827\charrsid16398449 fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 st and keys and all - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 knock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
 'em - there was many a one set about like that. And they got away with it you know because they said he was drunk and he was fell against the wall or something like that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
 - when Brockie Price was drunk he always come out with a black eye or something like that you know. Oh aye. Of course he didn't remember it - he was that drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Didn't know how he got his black eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
How did you spend your Saturdays when you were a child in Hankey Park - what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well we used to - got to the baths - or in the cut, oh aye. We went in cut, it was clean because you see all the works such as Elkahahs, Walkers and Carvers, all like that, all their hot water used to come from the boilers - and it was t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
rown into the cut. So and we was always in there with it being warm - we'd stop in nearly all day then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 They were cotton mills weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes
. Alkanahs - aye. And Alkanahs - and Walker Carvers was the paper works you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 
And - we - one time I'll never forget that - you see, we had to take us clothes off, was always stripped, no shorts to put on, nothing like that you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
We used to wrap us 
clothes up on the canal bank and just leave it there you know. Well, the other side was the forge. Pendleton Forge. And - the is policeman - many a time we used to - if he could get hold of us clothes we could get'e, on our put 'em on us head you know, th
e bundles - walk across, it wasn't very deep you know in some places. And - and put them over the other side so - and the policeman couldn't come over there - he couldn't get - over water - so we was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 plaguing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  you see
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Why did you plague the policeman - why did you take your clothes over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
So he - so that he wouldn't get hold of 'em. He - he'd keep them there so - until we come out you see, or else he'd take 'em, fetch 'em home. To where you lived. He'd summons you just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Just for swimming in the canal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 For bathing - oh yes. Oh that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
What happened when he took your clothes - you came home in your birthday suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
But he didn't get 'em you see, he didn't get 'em - we knew he were going to do that if he come and then we took 'em over to the other side - put them agen the forge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you see a lot of police in Hankey Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did you think of them and how did they treat the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well, they was - they was very bad some of them, and some was ve
ry good. Now - I will tell - I told you about absconding didn't I, from the - from the Caledonia - well, when I came - came here I had been here not - not two hours when somebody told the police I was over here you see. So - he came. And one was Haydock -
 
Louie Haydock and - there was Jack Hayes, he were Inspector Hayes at finish - Hayes - there was Jack Hayes, Lorner - Pat - Jack and Farrington, them was two - two detectives and Sam Brownley, he was another one and - George Morris. Now he kept the Rose an
d Crown you remember, he worked in the - it's only a few years ago since he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How do you think they treated the people as a whole though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well some was very good. And I was telling you about this Sam Barber when he took me back. He took me back t
o Queens Ferry. And - that's how I got away with it. I got to being discharged over this and he told me - he says, oh, he says, now Arthur, he says, I'm only - I've only got - I've not got very long to go now off me pension, you see, and he says I know yo
u
 - I know you could get away from me but I don't want to handcuff you or anything like that. Now the first time I was caught this Haydock, you see, he - handcuffed me. Now, it took over eleven hours to get; to Queens Ferry and he - if he wanted to go to t
h
e toilet or anything like that, instead of taking me with him he used to fasten me to the - arm - the form on the platform. Where everybody - I was exposed to everyone you see, which showed me up you see. So - I told - when I - when I said I'll come back 
a
gain I'll make you like it - just like that to this Haydock. Well when I come back a second time and - Sam Barber was taking me back - he says, now Arthur, he says, I'm - nearly on pension. He say, and it's my duty to take you but he - he was Inspector - 
I
nspector Barber, and he says, I want you to - to come nicely with me, he says, and inside that little portmanteau there - it's all for you - that's food for you while we get there. He was a gentleman. So - when he got - when I got back on the ship he says
 I'll just - told the - Captain, the Skipper, he says - I've just brought this - this boy - called me a boy you - know, 'cos I was only a boy - I've brought him from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 Salford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  where he's - where one of the police caught and brought him and - he say, this lad,
 he's gone through a lot. And - I don't think he's suitable to be on this ship. It would be better if you was to stretch it for as much as you could you see. Well when I got birched that time and - the doctor put that - as well you see. So - they give me 
that twenty-four cuts of the birch and - sixty days leave and pocket money stopped and my long vacation leave and then I had to wait for the Queens reprieve - Queen Victoria was then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You had to wait for what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 The Queen's sanction. Discharged - yes. Her Majesty's Service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Were you ever frightened by policemen - did your mother ever say, I'll tell the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Me mother was - sick of tired or policeman coming to door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 She never threatened you with the police at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh it was no use - we could get in enough - naughty. Said where you going. I said - she said the way they're going on they'll be - the way they're going on she said, they're going to be hung. They way they were - well they keep on being these fines and fi
nes. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did you do on Sundays ; did you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, never went to church love. No. It was foot - footballing and cut again and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You never went to any church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Didn't your mother and father go?
