\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you say family prayers - did anyone teach you to say your prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Only at - only at school. That's all. The -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You didn't say prayers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Nor grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. Only I say - I say 'em night and morning now you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You've got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 ood boy in your old age then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh aye. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, there was only - there was
 - there was Liberals and Tories - that's all there was then and they used to - politic people, you know. That was - and there was Elkanah Armitage, he was one and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 He'd be conservative wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Aye, that was the Conservative Coub he owned 
down Fleet Street - big place. Say he had it up there and there was oskew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you remember your father voting before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Voting? Oh me father used to go - yes. 'Course we weren't old enough then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you remember who he voted for and why he voted for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
I don't think - he knew what he was doing. Well he just - he just put it down. He didn't know what there was - I don't think that he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Of course he couldn't read or write could he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 So where did he put the cross?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Put it where he could - where he see - first thing he see - looked at I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh she never went. She could neither read nor write you know. Never went. There was no such things as going to the houses for people to vote. Oh no. It was John Street Hall they used to vote at you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 So whatever name he saw first got his vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
That's right. He don't know if he thought - or what they was - what they was voting for or nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 When your paren
ts weren't doing their work how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh well - father was - always went to beer house - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did he ever take your mother with him.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, mother never tasted drink in her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did he ever go to clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, he was no club sort. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Did your mother have any interests outside the home - was there anything went out of the house to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 I never knowed her to go out love at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did she never go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, no. There was no places like to go to. The only one was the hippodrome you know, but - that was - that was a op - pop bottle shop when things was going then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Did your father stay in many evenings when he came home from work or did he go out a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 He went up straight to bed. Aye. Now he'd say - say to me, now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 This is the nights he didn't go in the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. He'd - now Arthur - are you coming to bed with me and I'll give you tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Why did he want you to go to bed with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
To quieten him. To talk to him like when he went to sleep. And then next morning he'd give me tuppence. Well next morning he'd say, now - there was three of us. There was me and Freddie and Tommy. But he thought a lot about me you know. So 
- he says, who'll give me tuppence he says, for a good breakfast.? So of course I said, me, I'll give you tuppence dad. I'd give him the tuppence he give me the night before for going to bed with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You used to talk him to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Couldn't he sleep unless somebody talked to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 -No. No. Then he'd go all at once then. Off he'd go to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did he take part in any sport at all or did he go to the races or have a bet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. You see, there was no - the only races there was,
 you see, was down where - where number nine dock is. Now that was the racecourse. Yes. That's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Not where it is now?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, no. Oh no. It's before that love. And - the last - race there was - was a horse called Rambling Katie and it won the la
st one there at - there and it - one the first race here when it opened here. And - that was called - the whatsit - what do you call that place - Skinners Hill they call it. Well, we used to go on top of that and we could see the races you see. Now it's d
own there, you'll see it - Race Street, it used to be the racecourse down Chapel Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did your dad never have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, he never was a better, he - he'd no money to get - bet with love. He used to have it for beer. He only got a pound a week. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Whatever money he had he spent on beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. Used to give me mother about perhaps eighteen shillings and he'd have two bob left you know. Well it went a good way. The -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How often would he go to the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 He used to go every day - every night. When he had - when he had money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And the other nights he used to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
He used to stop in the house you see and I used to read to him - used to get me to read to him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 The paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh - oh we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you like each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
I never forget - I'll never forget one time with Tommy. I was always quick for him you know. And - with - with boxing gloves in the house you know - and there was a pl
ace like that - now we lived at sixty-two Rossall Street then and - next door was Mrs Booth lives at sixty. And - our house was back to back, you know, with theirs. Well there used to be a recess there and me mother used to hang all the toasting forks up 
there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Why did you have so many toasting forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well we used to - use a lot of toast you know and she used to - we used - used these toasting forks and they was hung up there. She used to hang 'em up there so as - you know, so as she get 'em }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  
- when want to toast - make a bit of toast. And there was that - sort that hangs down like that and two prongs sticks out. Well they was hung up there and me - me and Tommy were having ago. Father was in bed. And - I hit Tommy and - I knocked him against 
t
his here whatsot - and toasting fork stuck straight in his behind here. He screamed the place down - father come downstairs. He was looking for the - I dashed out - I dashed out of the house and - another time me mother was that vexed - there used to be a
 fellow come round with a milk dandy you know. You get your milk - a dandy it was - a big dandy it was - and me mother's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 The dandy was the thing that held the milk.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, full of milk. And - Tommy's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 arguing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  with me mother - teasing her you know
 and she's got a big ham bone - we used to get ham bones you know from the shops. Got fourpence for a ham bone - a lot of - a lot of meat on it you know, ham. And me mother used to have this when she - she's eat - eating it. -And he's - Tommy's teasing he
r
 you see and this fellow's outside with his milk - milk dandy and the door's open and - says I'll give you - wait 'til I get hold of you, you know. She's like this you see. Say, I know - Tommy says it'll take you long to catch me. So; she throws this bone
 at him. Throws the bone at him and he ducks and it goes through the door straight in this fellow's dandy. For milk. Ham - big ham bone.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What happened - did she have to pay for the milk or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, we shut door. Another time - another time - yo
u know when it was - fifth of November - Guy - called it Guy Fawkes - Guy you know. They come - they come to door you know and me - me and me mother's sitting in the house and - shouting Buy Fawkes - Guy - poke him in the eye. And she - they're there agai
n she says. I said, I'll shift 'em in minute. I said but don't let on Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 These were children were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. Just like myself you know. I goes outside and I gets brush - I gets brush. And they had this here Guy Fawkes, I thought it was a Guy F
awkes, and he said poke it - Guy Fawkes, Guy Fawkes, poke him in the eye. And when I did that I poked his belly you know. I said, he fell over - it was a lad. Was a little kid they had with 'em you see. And they'd paint - blacked his face and put a mask o
n him. My mother played hell with me. Me mother - I'd done it again - I was always in trouble. Kid - little kid screamed - I thought -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Was there anyone you were especially close to - that you thought a lot of in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you mean my brothe
rs? Well - only a little girl - Nellie. Thought a lot about her but she was only five years old when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You were fond of her were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh aye, she thought the world of me and all of it. Only wanted to go with me everywhere I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Wh
o did you play with when you were a child - your brothers or sisters or neighbours and where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well, we never - we never took the girl out, she was too young you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you play with neighbours children or just your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh aye, there was - we were all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Where did you play - apart from the cut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh aye, we was - we was in canal you know and sometimes we'd go down Bank Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Never play in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh aye. I'll tell you about that. When we we
re - when the mother used to - we used to go - she went out you see, before I could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 fetched}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  them in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 She wouldn't have them in if she was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, no. So she had to - said, aren't you going out today mum? Aye, I'm going out she says, but I 
- I'm going to keep me eye on there. Just like that. I said, why? I know, she says, you're after fetching them in here again. Well - one of 'em - it was Philly Jerrett his name was - that was the wife's brother - her name was Jarrett. And - thought the wo
r
ld of him, pal of mine he was. He was - was out in France with me. And - he was in the ranks - in the - North Lancs. So - I used to get - I had a hose pipe you know, and we used to get in yard - we didn't go in cut, we used to wash us some road you see. S
o I said now get stripped now I said and well' have a good - have a good do - I'll wash you and you can wash me. And - he gets stripped and I get the hose pipe and squirt it on him in yard and me mother come in - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 cached}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  me. She said pick that hose pipe up a
nd she battered me. 'Til I run out of house - oh dear, dear me. That's - that's what thou wants me out for isn't it.? So thou can fetch they - fetch the mates in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What games did you play?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Not the blood tub on Ellis Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh no. No. No. U
sed to go - we used to go up the Prince of Wales you know in Liverpool Street, you know. Aye that was the blood tin. Now - the one that was called the - down Gardener Street, next to the library you know. It was near the school, yes, I know Whilely had th
a
t and you used to get cups of coffee you know and you got coffee while they was on - sixpence to go in and you used to get a cup of coffee and a biscuit for the old people, you know, people used to go on - young men and all. And - that was a - that was th
e only one we went - went to Prince of Wales' you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was this while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, I was about ten or eleven when I went to - to Wales's. And - I used to go with with the wife - me wife, 'cos she was - well, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  then. Oh aye, she wa
nted to go to Prince of Wales's. Up to Nomah and face at Window and one thing and another you know. I'll never forget - I'll never forget that - we'd just been to see Prince of - Face at Window at Prince of Wales's and coming out coming down Liverpool Str
e
et we used to take a short cut to come over - come over the bridge you know. Take a short cut over the - cotton milling bridge you know. And there used to be placards of this produ - about this Face at - Face at the Window - and it were a awful face you k
now and just as we're turning round the corner wife was - well she wasn't - wasn't - we wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  then but - she turned round and she see'd this here and it was just like lifelike you know - with it being dark at night and - I thought she were in a fit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did your parents give you any pocket money and how much and how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, not so much - we used to make it - going about selling papers and different things you know, you get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 This is when you were a child at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did you get a job like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well we - it was Moore's - still Hankinson Street, that used to be the paper shop - lefthand side. Finished the paper shop - next to that was the beer house, you know. And we used to go - they was fourpence ha'penny for 
a dozen. Of papers. And we - we used to get - for every dozen we used to get a penny and three ha'pence of him for getting - for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 selling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  'em you see. Was only a ha'penny each. The evening papers was only a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You didn't deliver them, you just sold them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Sold 'em in the street. Oh aye, and we used to shout all sorts to sell 'em you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Such as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Terrible murder in Pendleton and - anything we heard you know about - so and so and all these here. And they used to come and get 'em. Used to rush one another you know, wh's going to get first to get round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And you used to get threeha'pence a dozen for selling them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you give any of the money to your mother or was this yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. No - had it for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did the man who owned the shop treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh he was Master Moores - he called Moores and - he used to give us - we used to get threeha'pence a dozen for selling them you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh, you know, all sorts of - piggy - piggy and stick you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Ah that was a piggy on a stick and you used to hit the piggy and you catch it and - you - I broke many a window with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh dear, we used to get - you see, me father, he 
- it'd be a bit late when he got home at night you see, from the beer house. And we had to get in before he come. And if we was dirty we just washed ourself you see and he used to come in room wee whether we was clean or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were you allowed to play 
with anybody you wanted or were there certain children you weren't allowed to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
NO - oh that was - everybody - anybody at all. It was all - always pals all - all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were there any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you keep any pets or have any hobbies or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, we - I'll never forget one time there was dogs on the Crescent there. There was a pub there called - the Staff of Life and - it was Peter Bainbridge as had it. He was a serg
 - a serg - a police Inspector. And he'd - he'd two big dogs. One was a - one was a bull mastiff - and the other was a - an English - an English bull - dog. Well me brother Freddie, he used to go there and do bits for him, you know, when he was young - co
m
ing out of school. So, he says, hey Fred, will you - will you take - Pincher that was it - that was his name, Pincher. Take Pincher round a bit will you for a bit of exercise? So - he was a bulldog. He says, yes. So he fetched him home - come home to moth
e
r. And - in the back kitchen there was a fireplace there and the fireplace was concrete you see. So - he says I'm going an errand, he says - I'm going an errand mu, he says. And I - where can I leave - where can I leave him? She says tie - tie him to kitc
h
en - tie him to oven door in there - he'll be all right there. And there was a fellow used to call - called Bingey. He was a cripple fellow and he used to sell kippers and he used to shout when he was - whenever he come to her - are you there Mrs Turner? 
A
nd I do you want anything Mrs Turner? Well, this dog - Pincher was in back kitchen and he was a powerful dog. So as soon as he come - you want anything Mrs Turner? Well, Pincher's - dodges out of kitchen and pulls oven door with him - he pull - pulled ove
n door straight off. And he was got - and he got hold of this fellow up front and oven door got fast in between. Oh there was - what the bloody hell thou's fetched in here for? She said - wrecked me place - take him back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you ever go fishing or for walks? Or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well we never went fishing - there was nothing to fish - nowhere to fish, only in cut you know - there was only - no fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You never had a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh we always had running 
- used to do a bit of running you know and - that - boxing and -.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you go to theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh the - the one that we went to - it's a good many years ago you know - that was Whiteways.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes, we liked it so as to get the coppers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family? Say your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well I never - I never knew her to be ill. Never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What happened when the children were born - did she ever talk about it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, yes, she had - there was a midwife then - midwife - always remember the midwifes name - Mrs Goldstraw of Ellis Street you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 A midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 But who helped with the work - would the neighbours come in and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. They would help, yes, and - there was - the nurse that used to come, she used to - we hadn't much you know, no clothing or anything like that for - this - this nurse used to arrange for fetching it - she used to call it the bag or something and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 This was for the new baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, for the baby. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Where did it come from - the bag?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
She brought 'em from some place you know and - oh, I don't know where it was it come from but it was some - institute but where it was I don't know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 It wasn't from the Heywards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh Miss Heyward used - that was when she went up to the Heights you see, on top road. Years and years after - after we was all born. And - me mother was - she was about seventy - sixty-five when Miss H
eyward used to come and she died when she was eighty-four. And - used to call and - she used to tell me - tell me mother to - if you can't come send Arthur round to the house, and I used to go to the Hall you know - big place, yes, Miss - Miss Monica's.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did you feel about this - did you mind going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no, I didn't mind going at all because - she was a woman - a very good woman and she always - her clothing was always touching the floor you know when she was going about - very old woman. Miss 
Monica. Miss Isabel - Miss Monica was the best of the two. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You mean the kindest of the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes, yes. Because she knew - always used to say now - to the maid, you know - now Alice - get the master a chair now, make him a nice cup of tea wh
ile he's waiting - Oh yes. Oh yes, in the house - inside, yes. It was just like Pendleton Town Hall - the steps you know - big broad steps. Chomlea it was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well she had a sister lived acr
oss the road. Up to - she died. That was me Aunt Jane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes, I saw -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did she come to visit and did you go over to her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh she used to come across to me mothers - always in. And - there would be - there was me Aunt - the name was Howard - me mother's name was Howard before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
 you know - she lived at Windsor in the cottages there - they called them the stone - stone cottages, Windsor. And me grandmother had a little farm there - pigs and things you kn
ow. But I never saw - I never saw me grandmother alive but - went one time - said to me go and sharpen that knife if you want something to eat and - then cut something up here - got a pestel here - and I went in kitchen -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Pestel was a small pan wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes. And - I went in kitchen - it was dark - dark night you know and I saw this woman, and oldish woman against the sink and she - I told my mother - I come in and told my mother I said Mum, there's - your - there's an old - woman in kitchen. Sh
e asked me what she was like and I told her - she had a - a white bonnet on and a - a longish clothes and she said that was me grandmother. Although I never saw her in me - I never saw her alive you know and - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Were you frightened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh, wasn't frightened - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did your parents have friends - a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well in Rossall Street you know they was - she was always with neighbours you see. They'd come in and do any mortal thing for you, you know, one to the other. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You mean just to help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh yes, always like that and then - I'll tell you about - they used to come you know to get mother to tell their fortunes. Aye. Yes. Oh there were several people used to come. Used to come for that purpose you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did they just come casually - did you just visit each other any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well, me mother never went out to anybody's house, you see, they used to come - they used to come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Nor your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, not my father - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 When they came in were they given anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
They'd come - here you are Mrs Turner - all that this here, I knew what they'd come for as they used to tell me to go out you know, you see, what - and they used to send - send for that dragons blood that I was telling you one time for chemist shop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
They say that people used to make their own amusements in those days - if they had neighbours in how did they amuse themselves - did they make music or play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, there was no music then love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Not even sing songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. No, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What would they do when they came in apart from having their fortunes told?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
They'd talk about different things you know, there was always talking about - always talking together about so and so and so and so and - 'course they couldn't let me hear anything like that - used to tell me to go out you see. Get along out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
They say that before 1918 people were divided into different social classes or groups do you remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well there was - there w
as - in Rossall Street it was all one group like that you see - they was all the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
What about the other streets round about - were they all the same type of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh they were all the same type of people, yes, those - some sort of - jolli
fication you know and - these women'd have a bet now and again you know in the Oller - a sixpenny bet or one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you think of some people as being rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well there was - there was a only one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 - one old woman - that was Mrs }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Brown, that they didn't like because she was - she'd get drunk you know and then she'd - she'd talk about knocking all the people up with a poker and all this business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did she ever do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Aye she did. She hit Mrs - what -
 the wife's mother one time. And - to have - to get her own back, you see she used to wait when you was passing door and she'd have this poker behind her you see, yes, and she'd hit'em with it for passing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 For nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Nothing at all. Oh,
 so the wife's mother, Mars Jarrett - she went to her, she was passing and - you know them - Christmas stuff - olly - holly, very prickly. She had a bunch of that behind her you see and - when she passed Mrs Brown, Mrs Brown was going to hit her with this
 see, she hit her in face with this here whatsit, you know, you never seen such a face in all your life - scratched all her face with this here - all - all - holly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
You don't remember any other class of people other than the people in Hankey Park and the Miss Heywards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
In - in the street there was - we - every peop - we all - we knew every one of - each others you see, what they did and everything like that and - now there was Mrs - next door was Mrs Kelly. Now - she - used to do - well, I told yo
u about that, she liked to bet. And she was always getting the ringer going and getting these things dried you know, sometimes for first race is about half past two. Wring them out - get 'em dried - up to - up to Kershaws or - or whatsit in Ansell Park.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What happened if she lost all the bets on the day - nobody had any clothes?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well - they - she used to get 'em out at weekends you see. When they got the wages off the girls and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did a lot of people go to the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh lots of them love, ayes - lots of 'em. You'd be surprised -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Some people would go for food though not just for betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
You'd be surprised at the strokes that they used to do. They'd pawn anything you know. Notes to the pawnbroker and he wouldn't know bec
ause they'd got that regular of doing things you see that - same - same as last week Master Kershaw, you see. Well he never used to bother undoing 'em, you see. Same as a suit or anything like that. And - there was one fellow there - when where was what t
hey call a drawing their pension - that's the first of July pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Dulaly pension?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes, they call dulaly pension. Well, it's the first of July the pension. When you got it - you only got it you see every three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Who was it from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
The Army. Well, he had a pension book same as we have a pension book now. And - Kershaw, you see you wasn't allowed to pawn that - that - pension book. So if you gave it in you'd have to either wrap it in a waistcoat or wrap it in a shirt you see or a pa
ir of trousers - never matter what it was like - whether it was big hole in or doesn't matter about that. But it had to be wrapped you see. That was to get - you wanted - say you wanted five shillings - well - well you - when you got the pension - first o
f July - dulaly day and - he - he used to have on - five shillings - waistcoat. Well that pension book was in that waistcoat pocket.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And Kershaw knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Of course. He had that - that was his what - security. He knew very well that when first of July come - that was the next week, that he - he had to come and get that book out before he can get his pension.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Do - you ever remember being taught to treat some people differently from others? Were you ever told to touch your cap or call somebody Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh well, some - some of the teachers anyhow used to - Sir and Miss - Miss Greenhalgh was the Headmistress that - St Geroges - St Thomas's you know and - Garnet was the headmaster at John Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did anyone ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 called}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  your father - or mother Sir or Madam or show them respect in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh he though - it was always Mrs Turner - that's the way it was them days you know. Mrs So and So - Mrs Fenney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Who were the most important people where you lived in Hankey Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well 
there was the people where we sometimes used to shop at you see. Sometimes - at Mrs Sharples's - that was the corner shop - opposite the beerhouse, you know. And there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 She was considered important was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes, because - she was a - if 
mother wanted tom - to borrow a shilling or a couple of shillings you know I used to go and say, mother wants to know will you lend her two shillings well - father gets paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And she would do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Would she charge you interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh no. No. Because we used to deal - there - get stuff you know. 'Course five shillings go a terrible length - way then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you remember anyone else that was important in Hankey Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well - there was only the shopkeepers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Who d
o you think the shopkeepers mixed with - when they went out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh the - suppose they went together in the big houses something like that you know, I don't know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What about Parsons - who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 I don't know ab
out that. The - there were relieving officer you know, we didn't like them people you see, we - when we came back we - we was - nothing doing at all - no work you know, we had to go down to - there was no dole - there was no dole you know. - There was no 
- no dole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Tell me about the relieving officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Now we used to go down to - Eccles Road and - to the workhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Did any workhouse children ever come to your school? Do you remember workhouse children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh - oh yes. Yes, the children - 
they used to come - the biggest part of them used to come out of the workhouse you know. But - the - they wasn't living in the workhouse you know. Was on - on - on the - you see, when we went there first - it was a fellow called Slack and - he - he'd ask 
u
s - how - they go about it. And he come to the house and you'd anything in the house that was fit to sell he'd ask you to sell that to buy your food. Well, we had to go down there when the - and Dorothy went to - go down twice a week and break stones in t
he workhouse yard for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Your father was this or you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, me. Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh, just as I come back from the war. '14 - 1914. Come back again - come back in '18. And - there was nothing doing. It - it - there was no dol
e. Lloyd George said - said it was going to have it fit for the hero's to live in you know. Well you had to be a hero to live in because there was nothing. So we used to go down there and - had to break stones twice a week and we got four and sixpenny foo
d ticket - that was for food and four and sixpence for rent. Now that's all you got. And on that food ticket it said - no luxuries - no cigarettes or anything like that. Just bread, margarine, tea and sugar. Now that's all we had to get along with. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you wouldn't get meat or potatoes or anything then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No, no, you had to scrounge it some road or other love. Pawn what - you had and everything. We pawned many a thing - pawned everything, mother did. And - because she did - did her best you kno
w, she couldn't carry on much because you see we all left - home you see, early. We was always moved early - there and away, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Tell me about the workhouse children? Did they come to John Street school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 They used to come - they
 used to come to - not to school. They had a school of their own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 inside}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  the workhouse you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you ever see any of them though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh I saw 'em, we saw 'em many a time when we went down at the Wednesday and Fridays to break stones you know. The - the old fellows used to work selling firewood you know. Little cart and - round hat on and call things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Who do you think the teachers mixed with when they were out - of school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well, you see the - they mostly - lived - lived away you see, th
ey lived away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What about the bosses - who do you think they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well - I suppose they only mixed together with themselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Can you tell me what sort of people went to church and what type of people went to chapel - did you ever know anybody who went to church and someone who went to chapel and did you notice any difference in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Oh there was a lot of people going - off - of the estates such as - there was no band about same as Hankey Park but - the R.C.'s the Catho
lics children - they used to go to that St James's church you know - they was always there at Sunday morning of course they go in there and then you go in Royal and get drunk straight away and - that's the way they carried on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was there any prejudice against them in Hankey Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, we never bothered about evils and morals you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You didn't know anyone who went to chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well, nearly everybody in street went to church Sundays you know. Oh, aye, nearly all Catholic near th
ere. Aye. This was that and - anyway - there was one chap I'll never forget. Alec McTanner his name was. And this priest came - and he says, hello Aleec, how're you going on? He says, I don't see you - I didn't see you in in church on Sunday Alec? So he s
aid, no, I didn't see you in pit last Monday either. So that was that. He wasn't a - a Catholic you know, but he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  one. And - I didn't see you in pit either last Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you find that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 Catholics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  were frightened of the priests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh, ay
e. More frightened of a priest than a policeman. Oh - a police - a priest could quieten them quicker than any policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How did he quieten them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
By his religion I suppose - he had them that way. Now there's one Rev - Jack Meacham. Now he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  a - a woman called - Mrs - what was her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 name}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  now - anyway - Sofphia Lynch. Sophia Lynch that was. So - he - he was a - a staunch Protestant you know and he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  - and - she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  him - she was Catholic. And this priest got to know. And he came to the house and told her that she was living with the devil because she'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11339473 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  him. So she told Jack Meacham about it and he went to that church, I thought he was going to kill him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did he do to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 He was going to set about him. And - we u
sed - the tricks they used to come in on these priests - they didn't - I don't know how they put up with it. Told when he went down there - and there was Kate Sandy. Kate Sandy - he come to her and he says I believe you've - you've been associating with t
h
at Protestant again - take you blouse off. Made her take her blouse off in the house. She told us this herself and - hit her with a stick like that on - on - on her bare breasts like that. But that - oh, he was a ; what - seafaring man. But he was going t
o do him and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 But they never touched the priests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Was there anybody in your district that was referred to as a real lady or a real gentleman - did you ever hear anyone described like this and why do you think it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well -
 the best natured man as ever I knew was a bookmater. Yes, that was Freddy Mush. Freddy Watson his name was but they called him Mush because he used to - when he first started he used to sell umbrellas. And they called - they called the umbrella a mush th
en - a mush.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was it short for musroom do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
I don't know what it was but they were calling him Freddy Mush. And he was a - he was a very good fellow. He used to boy us clogs and things you know and - and every night I believe he used to g
o to the - the beer houses where these punters used to associate and every Thursday night he used to pay for drinks all round the beerhouse - every Thursday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 You thought of him as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 I did - well that's what they say of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was there anyone you thought of as a real lady in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well - there's not - there wasn't so many well off down there but - there was only Miss Heyward you know, there - she was a lady. One or two people that - well they wasn't to say well off you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Did your father and mother have the same attitude to people in all classes - did they treat everybody alike?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, yes, everybody was the same. Yes, never - there was no }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14431977\charrsid16398449 discreet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449  between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What class so you think your mother thought she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well, you see, -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What class do you think you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well, I don't know really - I never see the - you know - she was never out of the house you know. Never out of the house at all. People used to come and see 
her but she never used to go in and out - up to her dying - she was in the - she was in Williamsons Buildings -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Your mother didn't notice any class distinction at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No. No. She treated one like the other. Everyone was the same - she never fell out with anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you think your father noticed any distinction in the classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, he was - he was a man that was always on his own like the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Do you think it was possible to move up in the world in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No you couldn't do love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
You could - you could - you've no - you've nothing to - to get you in the world - you've nothing - no wages, no money you see. You couldn't go anywhere - it went a good way as regards the food you see but we - we never drawed any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you ever know anybody who moved up in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No, I don't know one. Not in our days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Or anybody who went down in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No. Well, I mean to say, going down - well, there was one in our road - that was that brother of mine, Tommy, you know. He was a greengrocer and he was up in the world at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 So your brother moved up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Aye. For the time - he was a firm at - he was a greengrocer you know and he'd start with a basket and he'd go round with a basket on 
his head. About - about two or three months after that he'd have a donley and cart. And then he'd get to a pony and cart. And he had three shops all together. Now he was a fellow that - he couldn't - if he - if he went to - once - as he used to - he would
n
't - he wasn't satisfied with his own wife. That's why I didn't like him for that. He wasn't satisfied so that he went - he went out one time and sold his pony and cart to - to Needham and he went away with a woman called Dublin Ginny. Dublin Ginny. She w
a
s - she was a prostitute. And - his wife squandered - he went - he went to Liverpool with her and - she robbed him of what he had which served him right and - he sent word back to his wife and asked her would she send him his fare back to Liverpool. And s
he was silly enough to do it. Nicer woman as ever you saw in your life was Tish. Her name was Tisha.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Was it short - for Patricia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
No - for a Leticia. Leticia. And - this - this Heyward and all on the Estate - got to know about him going away and 
they said - Miss Heyward came and another lady. Now Mrs Turner, now - you look after yourself - she had a little shop at the High at the time and - and we'll always appreciate you and see that you're all right. And - she went and sent him money to come ba
c
k. And while they were talking he was in back - in the back kitchen. Well they didn't think much of her after that. Well I didn't either - me mother didn't either. And - he went - me father went with him one time to the Market. He had a very fast pony and
 
it was - it was summertime when all clubs and things were out you know and - special lot of stuff back with him. And me father - he got me father - he got me father - one or two drinks. And - he's no room up front with pony you know, so me father's on top
 
with these humper of plum - plums and things you know and it was a very fast pony and he was terror for getting him along going - wanted to go quick and when they were coming up Broad Street - he got in the tram lines with his cart and - and he gives a bi
t of a twirl like that there - me father went and when he was going he picked - he grabbed on of the hampers of plumb - and over he went. All the plums all over the tram lines and they were - oh, me mother started. Going away, she said, with that rascal.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Your house in Hankey Park was rented - how much did you pay for it - do you remember what the rent was in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Yes, yes. Four and three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Did you see your landlord at all and what did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh aye. He was a terror. John Thomas Godfrey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Why was he a terror?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well - he come sometimes and when he was for your rent - he'd say spent. That's the way they'd say to him you know. Bills and - in question - just bets and spending on horses and he - he'd get a thing - - 
taking his coat off to have a fight you know for your rent. Aye. He - he did one person down there - he wouldn't - he couldn't get no rent off him so he - he went and got a fellow from the Wagger and go and put a slate on top of - on top of chimney so he 
t
ry and smoke him out like. That's what he said - rents. Well them days - if you - we used to flit from one house to another. And all over. Go to Hayfield Street or go to another street. If there was house empty you used to go to the - the woman and give h
er a shilling for the key. Well we used to get the - the key and - go and fetch the furniture in and get - stop in that house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What was called a moonlight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Yes, yes. And then they'd - they'd perhaps stop in that house about - until - and 
keep missing rent - there you see until the - you - he - he was going to - he was going to throw them out so they got another one - going in perhaps from Rossall Street to Earl Street - only next street and house is empty - used to have plenty of houses e
mpty then days. Used to go from one house to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
When you were young did you feel your parents had a job to make ends meet and what did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Oh - dear, dear, many a time like that love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 
Well it - it - it got us that road that we couldn't see the old woman short or anything like that. You know we - we was going - we - what we got many a time and going to - to take things and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 How do you mean, take things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 Well used to
 have all the stuff outside at one time - outside the shops you know. We - we - two or three others we'd go together with a - we'd have a bag you know and there was a - we'd perhaps take a couple of tatoes out - out of that bag and get it somewhere else a
nd get onions you know - where there was onions. We'd get a - a dinner that way and take it to the old woman and let her stew it up - she'd know where it come from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 And you never got caught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14111072 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5445667 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5265281\charrsid16398449 When you started full time work did it ma
ke any difference to your relationship with your mother and father?
